<pre><code>class GameSystem &lt; ActiveRecord::Base   has_many :cartridges end  class Cartridge &lt; ActiveRecord::Base   belongs_to :game_system end </code></pre>  <p>I want to be able to do:</p>  <pre><code> GameSystem.joins(:cartridges)    .where({:cartridge =&gt; { :name =&gt; 'Dragons Lair', :publisher =&gt; 'Cinematronics' })    .where({:cartridge =&gt; { :name =&gt; 'Zaxxon', :publisher =&gt; 'Sega' })    .limit(1) </code></pre>  <p>In other words, tell me if there exists a game system where there was a Dragon's Lair cartridge by Cinematronics, AND a cartridge named Zaxxon by Sega...</p>  <p>Is there an activerecord friendly way to do this?</p>